## üé® Design Principles

### 1. Dark Theme First
- Deep green-black (#0F2B1F) creates a premium, focused experience
- Reduces eye strain for fitness tracking
- Green accents pop dramatically against dark surfaces

### 2. High Contrast
- White text on dark backgrounds ensures readability
- Vibrant green (#00FF87) for CTAs creates clear visual hierarchy
- Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for text

### 3. Generous Spacing
- Ample white space prevents clutter
- 16px minimum between interactive elements
- Use spacing to create visual hierarchy

### 4. Rounded Corners
- 8-16px border radius creates modern, friendly aesthetic
- Consistent rounded corners throughout app
- Softer appearance that feels approachable

### 5. Progressive Disclosure
- Show only essential information initially
- Use expandable sections for details
- Multi-step onboarding breaks complexity

### 6. Clear CTAs
- Primary action always uses green button
- Only one primary CTA per screen
- Secondary actions use outlined style

### 7. Consistent Iconography
- Use icons to support text, not replace it
- Maintain consistent icon style throughout
- Icons should be immediately recognizable

### 8. Feedback & States
- Provide immediate visual feedback for interactions
- Show loading states for async operations
- Clear selected/active states

